I am 18. Yes, it's legal.

The link below includes a letter from the ATF confirming the legitimacy of these types of transactions.

http://myfreedomfoundation.com/blog/liberty-live/detail/can-individuals-between-18-and-20-purchase-and-own-handguns> 

The statutes below were taken directly from LexisNexis.com (2014), which is the official site that Georgia uses to post and update it's new and existing laws.

O.C.G.A. § 16-11-132
Possession of a handgun by a person under the age of 18 years

Georgia law only covers possession of handguns by those 
"Under" the age of 18 with varying circumstances, as well as those 21+. That means a person 18-20 can legally "posses" a handgun.


O.C.G.A. § 16-11-101.1
Furnishing pistol or revolver to person under the age of 18 years

This law relates to the sale of handguns in Georgia through a private party (you and I) sale. Once again, it only refers to those "under" the age of 18. The rest of the laws that apply to the sale of handguns and handgun ammunition in Georgia are federal laws which only apply to an FFL or manufacturer. (http://www.nraila.org/gun-laws/articles/2004/citizen%60s-guide-to-federal-firearms-law.aspx> 

O.C.G.A. § 16-11-126
Having or carrying handguns, long guns, or other weapons; license requirement; exceptions for homes, motor vehicles, and other locations and conditions; penalties for violations

A person of age 18-20 is treated as an adult who does not have a Georgia Weapons Carry License, and must abide by those same rules. Those rules, in short, mean that the handgun may not leave the confines of my home (property of said home included), motor vehicle, and/or place of business

You will have to retrieve the glock 19 from my glove compartment and place the revolver in the former's previous location.

title: For Sale:  Adcor Defense 2012040E B.E.A.R. Elite Piston AR-15 16" 30+1 Optic Ready Magpul
postcontent:
B.E.A.R. (Brown Enhanced Automatic Rifle) models from Adcor Defense feature
a patent-bearing, gas piston system with a free-floating barrel for
increased accuracy. This is due to the piston's incorporation into the
upper half of the forward rail system - so it never touches the barrel.
Extremely close machine tolerances eliminate the need for piston rings. 
With a tool-less field strip design, a B.E.A.R. requires nothing more than
a firing pin to disassemble, yet remains strong. The piston's cyclical rate
for a controlled rate of fire adjusts with a turn of the gas plug located
in the front piston assembly. Because diminished heat reaches the upper,
hot gases and carbon particulates are prevented from entering the receiver,
lubricant lasts longer and maintenance is simplified. Due to superior
design, the B.E.A.R. has no carrier tilt and low fouling of the chamber and
action. The ejection port wiper prevents the entry of dust, sand and other
debris by moving into the ejection port opening flush with the inside
geometry of the upper receiver. The spring-loaded shield allows the bolt
carrier to return to ready position. Being made of a highly-durable,
self-lubricating polymer helps the shield withstand temperature extremes.
The B.E.A.R. Elite series features a few upgrades, including a Magpul MOE
rifle stock and Magpul MOE ergonomic rifle grip with aggressive texturing
for a sure grip. The chrome-lined barrel from FN Manufacturing has 1:7
twist and is hammer-forged with a M249 rifling profile for long life and
exceptional accuracy. It also has a forward-placed, ambidextrous charging
handle. It has a two-piece key-locked, highly-rigid quad-rail system made
of aircraft-grade 7075-T6 aluminum alloy that seamlessly mounts to the
upper receiver made from the same aircraft-grade 7075-T6 aluminum alloy.
The upper and lower rails separate with the push of a button - no special
tools required. NOTE. I ONLY ACCEPT WESTERN UNION AND MONEY GRAM, THEN WHEN I RECEIVED THE CASH THEN IT CAN BE SHIPPED.
